# Text Elements
TPP
1. Giving access to non guest-tek people
2. Having a TDE that manages TPPs 
3. TPPs are assigned to projects
4. The project status is determined by both an external database and the TDE
5. Page permissions for TPPs are managed by the TDE ^pzDgFgvV

Project Model
- FK: TDE in charge
- FK: TPPs (One to many)
- PK: id
- status: Intermediate steps
  - Existing statuses from myGuesttek
  - Fetch from myGuesttek
  - If status in "in progress" TDE can
    trigger a "signoff" state
  - If project is signoff, no TPPs have access
- name
- date of creation (fetch this from myGuestTek)
- hotel ID (One to many)


TPP Model
- PK: id
- FK: TDE
- FK: Project
- company (fetched from their email)
- email
- name
- creation date
- creation user 
- modification date
- modification user
- status: Active / inactive




 ^vo6yJM2r

Page Permissions:
- Per page basis: each page should be able to be accessible via permissions
- Whitelist users
- Whitelist roles
- An entry for all pages in the site
- Use the custom model that we have, or use the permissions system from Django
- Page hierarchy

User profile
- Meraki API key
- Profile picture 
- Under supervision of: Eustache ^AknNqlZv

bob@meraki.com ^7avEuF3v
